THE acting director of the National Institute for Sports (NIS), Dr Jimmy Adeniyi has declared that the foremost sport institute is proud of Nigeria Football Federation (NFF) Technical Director, Austin Eguavoen for registering for a management course with them. Eguavoen is among 143 students in coaching, management and marketing at the NIS in the 2021/2022 Academic session. Although Eguavoen was absent at the matriculation ceremony on Friday due to his busy schedule with US bound home based Super Eagles, Adeleye, said such bold initiative is commendable and welcomed.